Lorin-M-I.  Gaerlan-P-F.  Mandel-I-D.  Denning-C-R.

Composition of nasal secretion in patients with cystic fibrosis.

CYSTIC-FIBROSIS: me.  MUCUS: an.  NASAL-MUCOSA: se.

ADOLESCENCE.  ADULT.  ALBUMINS: an.  CHILD.  HUMAN.  IGA: an.
IGG:  an.  PHOSPHATES: an.  POTASSIUM: an.  PROTEINS: an.  SODIUM: an.
SUPPORT-U-S-GOVT-P-H-S.

Quantitative examination of nasal secretion in patients with cystic
fibrosis revealed a significantly greater than normal concentration
of calcium, a finding in keeping with the hypothesized importance of
this ion in the pathophysiology of the disease.

